1
00:00:01,068 --> 00:00:03,003
♪

2
00:00:18,785 --> 00:00:20,320
Gon: Ging?

3
00:00:22,289 --> 00:00:24,024
( Ging sighs )

4
00:00:24,091 --> 00:00:25,259
♪

5
00:00:25,325 --> 00:00:27,260
( Singing in Japanese )

6
00:00:53,620 --> 00:00:57,791
♪ You can smile again

7
00:00:57,858 --> 00:00:59,993
( singing in Japanese )

8
00:01:00,060 --> 00:01:03,664
♪ You can fly away

9
00:01:03,730 --> 00:01:05,665
( singing in Japanese )

10
00:01:15,742 --> 00:01:16,676
Ging: Hey.

11
00:01:20,547 --> 00:01:21,515
Gon: Ging!

12
00:01:21,582 --> 00:01:24,085
♪

13
00:01:25,152 --> 00:01:26,253
I’m sorry!

14
00:01:26,320 --> 00:01:27,521
It was all my fault.

15
00:01:27,588 --> 00:01:29,723
Because of me...

16
00:01:29,790 --> 00:01:32,126
Kite turned into a little girl!

17
00:01:32,192 --> 00:01:33,527
( Ging gasps )

18
00:01:33,594 --> 00:01:35,329
But the last I heard,

19
00:01:35,395 --> 00:01:37,130
he’d been captured by the enemy

20
00:01:37,197 --> 00:01:39,533
( Gon grunts ) Yeah,
I was with him when it happened.

21
00:01:39,600 --> 00:01:42,336
Then he told me to run away,
and pitou showed up.

22
00:01:42,402 --> 00:01:44,337
After that, kite lost his arm.

23
00:01:44,404 --> 00:01:46,539
i was knocked out,
and then we started training!

24
00:01:46,607 --> 00:01:49,176
Shoot was able to get kite
out of the ants’s nest,

25
00:01:49,243 --> 00:01:51,579
but it wasn’t
really him anymore.

26
00:01:51,645 --> 00:01:53,547
It wasn’t kite at all!

27
00:01:53,614 --> 00:01:56,217
And they--what they did to him,

28
00:01:56,283 --> 00:01:59,153
it was--it was horrible!

29
00:01:59,219 --> 00:02:00,253
( Ging gulps )

30
00:02:00,320 --> 00:02:01,588
( Sighs )

31
00:02:01,655 --> 00:02:05,526
Gon: And then, later on,
I ran into pitou again,

32
00:02:05,592 --> 00:02:09,496
who told me that--
that kite was already dead!

33
00:02:09,563 --> 00:02:11,365
Ging: Okay. I get it!

34
00:02:11,431 --> 00:02:14,701
Okay, maybe I don’t get it,
but sit down. Come on.

35
00:02:14,768 --> 00:02:17,371
Uh, thing is...

36
00:02:17,437 --> 00:02:18,638
Let’s just calm down.

37
00:02:18,705 --> 00:02:20,707
We both ought to,
so just try to relax.

38
00:02:20,774 --> 00:02:23,010
Gon: It was because...

39
00:02:23,076 --> 00:02:25,512
I insisted...

40
00:02:25,579 --> 00:02:27,314
On having my way!

41
00:02:27,381 --> 00:02:30,184
ging: Anyway,
just calm down first.

42
00:02:30,250 --> 00:02:31,518
We can talk this over.

43
00:02:31,585 --> 00:02:33,387
List: Ging is...

44
00:02:33,453 --> 00:02:34,521
Dwun: Caught off guard?

45
00:02:34,588 --> 00:02:36,323
I’ve never seen him like this!

46
00:02:36,390 --> 00:02:38,192
Gon: It’s not fair!

47
00:02:38,258 --> 00:02:40,727
If anyone had to die,
it should have been me!

48
00:02:40,794 --> 00:02:42,329
Ging: Eh?

49
00:02:42,396 --> 00:02:43,364
Gon...

50
00:02:44,431 --> 00:02:46,133
That’s not true.

51
00:02:46,200 --> 00:02:49,203
There’s a reason
he took you along,

52
00:02:49,269 --> 00:02:52,239
because he thought
you could handle the mission.

53
00:02:52,306 --> 00:02:54,742
He underestimated the enemy.

54
00:02:54,808 --> 00:02:57,311
that’s why
he told you to run away.

55
00:02:58,779 --> 00:03:01,482
He thought he was up to the task
from the start.

56
00:03:01,548 --> 00:03:04,284
If he hadn’t, he wouldn’t have
taken you, no matter what.

57
00:03:04,351 --> 00:03:07,487
He just misjudged the enemy.
That’s all.

58
00:03:07,554 --> 00:03:08,488
Gon: Yeah, but--

59
00:03:08,555 --> 00:03:10,257
ging: Yes, I know.

60
00:03:10,324 --> 00:03:13,093
you just weren’t
strong enough to help him,

61
00:03:13,160 --> 00:03:15,396
so you can take
some responsibility for that.

62
00:03:15,462 --> 00:03:16,997
Gon: Mm-hmm.

63
00:03:17,064 --> 00:03:19,099
Ging: Don’t make
the same mistake again.

64
00:03:19,166 --> 00:03:21,268
And if there’s anyone
you should apologize to,

65
00:03:21,335 --> 00:03:23,003
it’s kite, not me.

66
00:03:23,070 --> 00:03:26,407
from what you said,
i’m not sure he’s dead yet.

67
00:03:26,473 --> 00:03:28,508
Just go! Apologize!

68
00:03:28,575 --> 00:03:31,111
( Gon sighing )

69
00:03:31,178 --> 00:03:33,714
Ging: But friends
apologize differently.

70
00:03:33,780 --> 00:03:35,348
Do you know how?

71
00:03:35,415 --> 00:03:38,118
( Gon gasps )
Mm-mmm. Tell me.

72
00:03:38,185 --> 00:03:40,421
ging: You have
to make them a promise.

73
00:03:40,487 --> 00:03:42,155
tell them
what you’ll do next time,

74
00:03:42,222 --> 00:03:45,125
and then you keep
that promise, no matter what.

75
00:03:45,192 --> 00:03:47,061
( Gon sighs )

76
00:03:47,127 --> 00:03:48,128
( Grunts )

77
00:03:48,195 --> 00:03:49,596
Ging: Now get going!

78
00:03:49,663 --> 00:03:50,631
Gon: Right!

79
00:03:54,201 --> 00:03:55,135
Ging...

80
00:03:55,202 --> 00:03:56,537
Ging: Hmm?

81
00:03:56,603 --> 00:04:00,240
Gon: Can we talk more later on,

82
00:04:00,307 --> 00:04:01,475
if you can?

83
00:04:01,542 --> 00:04:03,377
( Ging grumbles )

84
00:04:03,443 --> 00:04:05,245
Yeah, that might be kinda tough.

85
00:04:05,312 --> 00:04:07,080
I’m a pretty busy guy, you know.

86
00:04:07,147 --> 00:04:08,081
( Crowd shouting )

87
00:04:08,148 --> 00:04:09,483
Man: Quit messing around, ging!

88
00:04:09,550 --> 00:04:11,085
You call yourself a father?!

89
00:04:11,151 --> 00:04:13,286
Man 2: Yeah! Come on,
you heartless jerk!

90
00:04:13,353 --> 00:04:15,288
man 3: I know
all about "greed island"!

91
00:04:15,355 --> 00:04:18,024
You never went to see gon
after he cleared it!

92
00:04:18,091 --> 00:04:19,292
What’s the deal?

93
00:04:19,359 --> 00:04:21,294
( Ging gasps )

94
00:04:21,361 --> 00:04:24,664
hey, shut up!
It’s none of your business!

95
00:04:24,731 --> 00:04:25,999
Woman: You’re the worst, ging!

96
00:04:26,066 --> 00:04:28,535
Man 1: You should
apologize to gon!

97
00:04:28,602 --> 00:04:31,538
promise him you’ll be
more like a father from now on!

98
00:04:31,605 --> 00:04:34,007
man 2: You don’t even
have the right to be his father!

99
00:04:34,074 --> 00:04:35,309
Ging: What the hell?!

100
00:04:35,375 --> 00:04:37,010
why don’t you
go screw yourselves?!

101
00:04:37,077 --> 00:04:40,414
man 3: You should
let leorio punch you again!

102
00:04:40,480 --> 00:04:43,383
Ging: Fine. Shut up.
You made your point!

103
00:04:43,450 --> 00:04:45,719
I’ll wait right here! Go!

104
00:04:45,786 --> 00:04:49,156
Man 2: You think we’re stupid?!
Take him there yourself!

105
00:04:49,223 --> 00:04:51,258
Man 1: You’re his dad, right?

106
00:04:51,325 --> 00:04:54,428
Ging: Hey! I’ve heard enough!
You wanna fight?

107
00:04:54,495 --> 00:04:57,431
if you got a problem,
then why don’t you bring it on?!

108
00:04:57,498 --> 00:04:58,599
( Shouting continues )

109
00:04:58,665 --> 00:05:00,600
what?!
You’re all my enemies now?!

110
00:05:00,667 --> 00:05:02,736
Okay! That’s fine by me!

111
00:05:02,803 --> 00:05:04,338
( Shouting continues )

112
00:05:06,440 --> 00:05:08,575
Piyon: Knock it off!

113
00:05:08,642 --> 00:05:10,077
Quiet down!

114
00:05:10,143 --> 00:05:13,980
( Microphone feedback )

115
00:05:14,047 --> 00:05:15,348
Cheadle: Thank you.

116
00:05:15,415 --> 00:05:17,384
This election isn’t quite over.

117
00:05:17,451 --> 00:05:19,286
( Thinking )
That’s right.

118
00:05:19,353 --> 00:05:21,355
I still haven’t given up.

119
00:05:22,656 --> 00:05:25,993
A new last chance has appeared.

120
00:05:26,059 --> 00:05:27,127
Now, gon--

121
00:05:27,194 --> 00:05:29,530
pariston: Stay right there!

122
00:05:29,596 --> 00:05:31,298
As you may well recall,

123
00:05:31,365 --> 00:05:34,401
no one is allowed to leave
until the election is over.

124
00:05:34,468 --> 00:05:37,037
I’m sure you have
somewhere else to be,

125
00:05:37,104 --> 00:05:38,472
but this will be the vote

126
00:05:38,539 --> 00:05:41,275
that ultimately decides
who our next chairman will be.

127
00:05:41,341 --> 00:05:43,610
you can leave
after you’ve cast your ballot.

128
00:05:43,677 --> 00:05:46,146
if you tell us
your choice right now,

129
00:05:46,213 --> 00:05:48,215
i’m quite certain
that everyone will agree

130
00:05:48,282 --> 00:05:50,217
to recognize it as a valid vote.

131
00:05:50,284 --> 00:05:52,219
( Crowd cheering )

132
00:05:53,687 --> 00:05:57,090
So between myself
and Mr. Leorio,

133
00:05:57,157 --> 00:05:59,626
who do you believe
would best fit the position?

134
00:05:59,693 --> 00:06:02,563
i should mention
that former chairman netero

135
00:06:02,629 --> 00:06:05,966
is on extended leave
after defeating the ant king.

136
00:06:06,033 --> 00:06:08,168
Cheadle: How dare you?

137
00:06:08,235 --> 00:06:11,038
How can you say that?

138
00:06:11,104 --> 00:06:14,074
if gon picks leorio
after his dramatic arrival,

139
00:06:14,141 --> 00:06:17,244
everyone may get caught up
in the heat of the moment again.

140
00:06:17,311 --> 00:06:20,047
you may have
just handed leorio the win.

141
00:06:21,248 --> 00:06:22,416
Gon: The chairman?

142
00:06:22,482 --> 00:06:24,517
Did leorio nominate himself?

143
00:06:24,585 --> 00:06:27,588
leorio: No way!
See, some stuff happened--

144
00:06:27,654 --> 00:06:28,989
pariston: Please, gon.

145
00:06:29,056 --> 00:06:32,192
i want you
to trust your instincts.

146
00:06:32,259 --> 00:06:34,194
Be true to yourself, all right?

147
00:06:34,261 --> 00:06:36,497
Then make your selection.

148
00:06:38,799 --> 00:06:41,669
Gon: Um, well...

149
00:06:41,735 --> 00:06:44,705
Then I pick Mr. Pariston.

150
00:06:44,771 --> 00:06:45,739
( Crowd murmuring )

151
00:06:45,806 --> 00:06:47,741
( Cheadle gasps )

152
00:06:47,808 --> 00:06:51,345
Pariston: But isn’t
Mr. Leorio your friend?

153
00:06:51,411 --> 00:06:54,648
I’m confused. You’re voting
against your own friend?

154
00:06:54,715 --> 00:06:56,183
( Gon grunts )

155
00:06:56,250 --> 00:06:58,385
because I know that
leorio wants to be a doctor,

156
00:06:58,452 --> 00:07:00,087
so he can’t be chairman.

157
00:07:00,153 --> 00:07:01,688
( Cheadle groans )

158
00:07:01,755 --> 00:07:03,690
( Leorio chuckles )

159
00:07:03,757 --> 00:07:05,492
Pariston: That makes sense.

160
00:07:05,559 --> 00:07:07,594
( Cheadle whimpers )

161
00:07:07,661 --> 00:07:10,297
This is it. I’ve been defeated.

162
00:07:11,365 --> 00:07:13,367
Pariston: I can appreciate that.

163
00:07:13,433 --> 00:07:16,303
And, if there’s nothing else,
let’s begin the vote.

164
00:07:16,370 --> 00:07:19,974
Leorio: Oh! By the way,
i’m siding with gon here.

165
00:07:20,040 --> 00:07:22,276
You’ve got my vote, pariston.

166
00:07:23,544 --> 00:07:24,545
Morel: Leorio.

167
00:07:24,611 --> 00:07:26,246
Leorio: Yeah, I know.

168
00:07:27,581 --> 00:07:28,682
Gon: Ging!

169
00:07:28,749 --> 00:07:29,683
Ging: Hmm?

170
00:07:31,618 --> 00:07:33,320
Gon: I’m gonna go now!

171
00:07:33,387 --> 00:07:35,322
( Ging sighs )

172
00:07:35,389 --> 00:07:36,323
Right.

173
00:07:36,390 --> 00:07:38,525
( Gon laughs )

174
00:07:38,592 --> 00:07:40,394
man 1: That all
you have to say, idiot?

175
00:07:40,460 --> 00:07:42,495
Man 2: You could at least say,
"see you later"!

176
00:07:42,563 --> 00:07:44,498
Don’t you have any decency?

177
00:07:44,565 --> 00:07:46,634
- ( Blows thumping )
- Aah! Ging’s lost it!

178
00:07:46,700 --> 00:07:50,103
Man 3: Quick! Somebody stop
this negligent jerk of a father!

179
00:07:50,170 --> 00:07:52,639
- Woman: That’s impossible!
- Man 1: Do something, zodiacs!

180
00:07:52,706 --> 00:07:55,642
( Gon laughs )

181
00:07:55,709 --> 00:07:58,645
I guess ging’s popular
in his own way, huh?

182
00:07:58,712 --> 00:08:01,281
( Leorio chuckles )
I don’t know.

183
00:08:01,348 --> 00:08:02,583
- Ging: Hey, gon!
- Leorio: Huh?

184
00:08:02,649 --> 00:08:04,684
Ging: I almost forgot.

185
00:08:04,751 --> 00:08:06,419
I’m the one who taught kite

186
00:08:06,486 --> 00:08:09,089
how to use his nen
and his techniques.

187
00:08:09,156 --> 00:08:11,458
Remember his crazy slots?

188
00:08:12,759 --> 00:08:14,394
Well, there’s a special number

189
00:08:14,461 --> 00:08:17,698
that only comes up when he
really doesn’t want to die!

190
00:08:17,764 --> 00:08:19,332
( Gon gasps )

191
00:08:19,399 --> 00:08:20,700
Ging: If he’s still alive,

192
00:08:20,767 --> 00:08:23,303
i’m willing to bet
that’s the reason why.

193
00:08:23,370 --> 00:08:26,373
I can tell you
one thing, though.

194
00:08:26,440 --> 00:08:29,510
he wasn’t trying
to sacrifice himself for you.

195
00:08:29,576 --> 00:08:32,112
apologize,
and do it the right way.

196
00:08:32,179 --> 00:08:34,682
Or else he’ll
kick your ass again!

197
00:08:37,484 --> 00:08:38,719
Gon: Right. No problem.

198
00:08:38,785 --> 00:08:40,720
Bye!

199
00:08:40,787 --> 00:08:42,722
ging: Right!
I’ll be waiting for you!

200
00:08:42,789 --> 00:08:44,124
( Men gurgle )

201
00:08:44,191 --> 00:08:47,127
- ( Blows thumping )
- ( Men grunting )

202
00:08:47,194 --> 00:08:49,063
( Gon gasps ) "Again"?

203
00:08:49,129 --> 00:08:51,498
♪

204
00:08:55,402 --> 00:08:56,536
( Sighs )

205
00:08:56,603 --> 00:08:57,537
Ging.

206
00:08:58,605 --> 00:09:00,307
♪

207
00:09:00,307 --> 00:09:02,109
♪

208
00:09:04,611 --> 00:09:06,079
( Microphone feedback )

209
00:09:06,146 --> 00:09:07,748
Pariston: Hello, everyone!

210
00:09:07,814 --> 00:09:11,017
I am pariston,
your 13th chairman!

211
00:09:11,084 --> 00:09:13,553
Now listen closely.
I have an announcement!

212
00:09:13,620 --> 00:09:14,554
( Cheadle gasps )

213
00:09:14,621 --> 00:09:16,423
Pariston: As the new chairman,

214
00:09:16,490 --> 00:09:19,193
I appoint miss cheadle
as vice chairman,

215
00:09:19,259 --> 00:09:21,728
and, with that,
I hereby resign my position.

216
00:09:23,497 --> 00:09:25,332
Ging: Oh. Uh, well...

217
00:09:26,867 --> 00:09:29,503
I sure didn’t see
that one coming.

218
00:09:32,840 --> 00:09:36,210
Cheadle: How long must you
make a mockery of everything?!

219
00:09:36,276 --> 00:09:37,244
Get back here!

220
00:09:41,348 --> 00:09:43,684
Pariston: When I
became vice chairman,

221
00:09:43,750 --> 00:09:47,287
it wasn’t because
I wanted to become chairman.

222
00:09:47,354 --> 00:09:50,490
I just wanted
to toy with netero.

223
00:09:50,557 --> 00:09:55,462
Whenever I said silly things
to try to get under his skin,

224
00:09:55,529 --> 00:09:58,665
Mr. Netero was always
so happily bothered.

225
00:10:00,467 --> 00:10:04,104
I only wish that we’d
had more time to play.

226
00:10:04,171 --> 00:10:05,673
( Cheadle gasps )

227
00:10:12,779 --> 00:10:16,516
Pariston: I recommend you reform
the hunter exam and bylaws soon.

228
00:10:16,583 --> 00:10:18,485
( Cheadle growls )

229
00:10:19,720 --> 00:10:21,522
( Pariston sniffles )

230
00:10:21,588 --> 00:10:24,324
Miss cheadle,
if the association

231
00:10:24,391 --> 00:10:26,793
becomes a dull place
under your leadership...

232
00:10:30,531 --> 00:10:33,834
next time,
i’ll pull your leg for real.

233
00:10:33,901 --> 00:10:36,804
( Cheadle gasps )

234
00:10:44,711 --> 00:10:46,313
Gon: Leorio...

235
00:10:46,380 --> 00:10:47,381
Where’s killua?

236
00:10:47,447 --> 00:10:49,316
Leorio: Huh? Oh, I don’t know.

237
00:10:49,383 --> 00:10:52,753
i’ve been calling,
but he won’t answer his cell.

238
00:10:52,819 --> 00:10:55,488
But it sounded to me
like he was traveling,

239
00:10:55,556 --> 00:10:57,525
looking for some way
to heal you.

240
00:10:57,591 --> 00:11:00,727
Well, i’m sure he’ll come
once we contact him.

241
00:11:03,197 --> 00:11:06,434
gon: I just--
I need to apologize to him.

242
00:11:06,500 --> 00:11:09,703
When I fought with the enemy,
I got real confused,

243
00:11:09,770 --> 00:11:12,706
and I said
terrible things to him.

244
00:11:12,773 --> 00:11:14,508
( Leorio sighs )

245
00:11:14,575 --> 00:11:17,745
Actually i’m sorry, too.

246
00:11:17,811 --> 00:11:21,348
Gon: Huh? But what do you
have to be sorry for, leorio?

247
00:11:21,415 --> 00:11:22,783
( Leorio sighs )

248
00:11:22,850 --> 00:11:25,619
When you guys really
needed help, I couldn’t.

249
00:11:25,686 --> 00:11:27,788
gon: Huh?
What are you talking about?

250
00:11:27,855 --> 00:11:29,223
I don’t understand!

251
00:11:29,289 --> 00:11:32,592
Leorio: Just know
i’m really sorry.

252
00:11:42,703 --> 00:11:45,439
illumi: The demands
following a wish for a computer

253
00:11:45,506 --> 00:11:49,810
should be more severe
than playing possum and hugs.

254
00:11:49,877 --> 00:11:50,811
( Bodies slump )

255
00:11:54,414 --> 00:11:56,650
the first moment
I realized something was off

256
00:11:56,717 --> 00:11:59,153
was when I heard
milluki’s report

257
00:11:59,219 --> 00:12:00,854
and when the binary choice wish

258
00:12:00,921 --> 00:12:03,223
resulted in a simple kiss
on the cheek,

259
00:12:03,290 --> 00:12:07,427
yet the price was a fingernail,
quite a heavy price, indeed.

260
00:12:09,596 --> 00:12:13,467
Assuming that the fingernails
were the price for the computer,

261
00:12:13,534 --> 00:12:16,404
that would match the balance
between wishes and demands

262
00:12:16,470 --> 00:12:19,573
that we had observed previously.

263
00:12:19,640 --> 00:12:24,111
If my theory is correct,
playing possum and the hug

264
00:12:24,178 --> 00:12:26,180
weren’t requests from nanika,

265
00:12:26,246 --> 00:12:30,250
and if that’s true, there’s only
one conclusion that makes sense.

266
00:12:30,317 --> 00:12:33,420
The binary choice wish
didn’t require a payment.

267
00:12:34,655 --> 00:12:36,724
Why was that the case?

268
00:12:36,790 --> 00:12:39,159
There are two possibilities
I can think of.

269
00:12:40,460 --> 00:12:42,862
One, because the wish
was simple enough

270
00:12:42,930 --> 00:12:46,700
that nanika’s power
wasn’t required to carry it out.

271
00:12:46,767 --> 00:12:51,272
Two, because it
wasn’t a wish at all.

272
00:12:52,739 --> 00:12:56,309
However, there’s still
an unresolved question.

273
00:12:56,376 --> 00:12:59,679
If playing dead and the hugs
weren’t demands from nanika...

274
00:13:01,315 --> 00:13:03,651
They were demands from alluka,

275
00:13:03,717 --> 00:13:06,220
not nanika, as we had thought.

276
00:13:07,688 --> 00:13:09,323
Killua claims that nanika

277
00:13:09,389 --> 00:13:11,524
always refers to him
by his proper name,

278
00:13:11,592 --> 00:13:16,097
but the demand to play dead,
that was made to "big brother."

279
00:13:17,331 --> 00:13:19,066
Thus it’s fair to say

280
00:13:19,132 --> 00:13:22,235
that the one who calls killua
"big brother" is alluka.

281
00:13:23,837 --> 00:13:26,206
If that request did,
in fact, come from alluka,

282
00:13:26,273 --> 00:13:29,209
we can assume nanika
wasn’t awake at the time.

283
00:13:29,276 --> 00:13:31,211
And if nanika was asleep,

284
00:13:31,278 --> 00:13:34,481
killua shouldn’t have been able
to make the binary choice wish.

285
00:13:34,548 --> 00:13:38,585
However, nanika responded
to killua’s wish.

286
00:13:38,652 --> 00:13:41,321
The hint to resolving
this contradiction

287
00:13:41,388 --> 00:13:42,856
lies in killua’s wording.

288
00:13:42,923 --> 00:13:44,591
when making
the binary choice wish,

289
00:13:44,658 --> 00:13:47,594
he wasn’t asking.
He was ordering.

290
00:13:48,662 --> 00:13:50,497
It does make sense that an order

291
00:13:50,564 --> 00:13:52,599
would work differently
than a wish and that,

292
00:13:52,666 --> 00:13:56,570
upon completion, it might
not require a price to be paid.

293
00:13:58,472 --> 00:14:01,041
Well, that’s my theory anyway.

294
00:14:01,108 --> 00:14:02,109
Am I right?

295
00:14:07,514 --> 00:14:09,249
I’ll get to the point.

296
00:14:09,316 --> 00:14:12,052
The zoldyck family needs someone
who can use nanika’s power

297
00:14:12,119 --> 00:14:16,056
safely and effectively,
and that person is me.

298
00:14:16,123 --> 00:14:18,392
As it stands, alluka is no more

299
00:14:18,458 --> 00:14:21,461
than a spirit locked away
forever in a room.

300
00:14:21,528 --> 00:14:25,232
That said, if I can control her
with you at her side...

301
00:14:28,368 --> 00:14:32,372
I can guarantee some freedom,
at the very least.

302
00:14:33,774 --> 00:14:35,476
Killua: Big brother...

303
00:14:35,542 --> 00:14:38,078
♪

304
00:14:46,553 --> 00:14:49,489
Don’t worry about it.
I’ll protect alluka.

305
00:14:49,556 --> 00:14:52,826
Illumi: Oh, kil,
know your place.

306
00:14:52,893 --> 00:14:55,829
Killua: Nanika, wake up.

307
00:14:55,896 --> 00:14:57,798
( Nen whooshes )

308
00:15:00,467 --> 00:15:01,768
Nanika: ’kay.

309
00:15:01,835 --> 00:15:03,737
♪

310
00:15:06,406 --> 00:15:08,375
( Men vocalizing)

311
00:15:08,442 --> 00:15:10,144
Illumi: All right...

312
00:15:10,210 --> 00:15:12,045
This is it.

313
00:15:12,112 --> 00:15:13,380
Let me have nanika--

314
00:15:13,447 --> 00:15:16,183
killua: Nanika, take illumi,

315
00:15:16,250 --> 00:15:18,119
and send him back home!

316
00:15:18,185 --> 00:15:20,387
Nanika: ’kay.

317
00:15:20,454 --> 00:15:22,389
( Vocalizing ends )

318
00:15:22,456 --> 00:15:24,325
( Mrs. Zoldyck gasps )

319
00:15:24,391 --> 00:15:25,392
( Illumi gasps )

320
00:15:25,459 --> 00:15:27,328
Milluki: Teleportation?

321
00:15:27,394 --> 00:15:28,495
Wait. For real?

322
00:15:28,562 --> 00:15:32,066
Illumi: I see.
You were watching us?

323
00:15:34,501 --> 00:15:35,635
That’s amazing.

324
00:15:35,702 --> 00:15:37,470
He’s invincible.

325
00:15:39,306 --> 00:15:44,111
there are no risks
when killua issues an order.

326
00:15:44,178 --> 00:15:45,780
And that means

327
00:15:45,846 --> 00:15:50,184
that turning killua
into my puppet is worth it.

328
00:15:51,451 --> 00:15:53,753
Killua: Tsubone, amane,

329
00:15:53,820 --> 00:15:57,123
can I ask you to leave us alone
for just a moment?

330
00:15:57,191 --> 00:16:00,294
If you don’t leave on your own,

331
00:16:00,360 --> 00:16:02,462
i’ll have to issue
another order.

332
00:16:03,530 --> 00:16:05,432
Nanika: Killua...

333
00:16:05,499 --> 00:16:07,434
Tell me I did good.

334
00:16:08,635 --> 00:16:10,036
Killua: Nanika only does this

335
00:16:10,103 --> 00:16:12,472
because she wants me
to praise her.

336
00:16:12,539 --> 00:16:15,242
I could just keep
issuing orders,

337
00:16:15,309 --> 00:16:17,344
but I don’t want
to use her like that.

338
00:16:17,411 --> 00:16:19,146
♪

339
00:16:21,181 --> 00:16:23,083
So please...

340
00:16:23,150 --> 00:16:24,618
Nanika: Killua.

341
00:16:26,753 --> 00:16:28,421
Killua.

342
00:16:29,756 --> 00:16:34,294
Killua. Killua.

343
00:16:35,596 --> 00:16:37,098
Killua: Nanika.

344
00:16:37,164 --> 00:16:41,201
nanika: Killua,
tell me that i’m good, okay?

345
00:16:42,569 --> 00:16:46,840
killua: Look,
you can’t come out anymore.

346
00:16:52,913 --> 00:16:55,716
Nanika: Killua, I love you.

347
00:16:55,782 --> 00:16:57,517
( Killua gasps )

348
00:17:01,822 --> 00:17:03,657
Killua: You can’t
come out, nanika.

349
00:17:03,724 --> 00:17:07,628
Nanika: I love you, killua.

350
00:17:07,694 --> 00:17:09,663
Killua, I love you.

351
00:17:09,730 --> 00:17:10,664
Killua: No!

352
00:17:10,731 --> 00:17:12,633
Don’t ever come out again!

353
00:17:12,699 --> 00:17:13,667
You hear me?!

354
00:17:13,734 --> 00:17:15,669
( Nanika whimpering )

355
00:17:21,141 --> 00:17:22,676
’kay.

356
00:17:24,211 --> 00:17:26,146
( Sighs )

357
00:17:32,586 --> 00:17:34,088
Killua: There.

358
00:17:34,154 --> 00:17:36,056
Now alluka can be free.

359
00:17:37,858 --> 00:17:40,694
( Sighs ) I’m sorry.

360
00:17:40,761 --> 00:17:42,630
I’m so sorry, nanika.

361
00:17:45,399 --> 00:17:46,333
I’m sorry.

362
00:17:48,769 --> 00:17:50,371
( Alluka sighs )

363
00:17:50,437 --> 00:17:51,505
( Killua gasps )

364
00:17:52,639 --> 00:17:53,673
Alluka?

365
00:17:55,175 --> 00:17:57,277
( Alluka sighs )

366
00:18:03,116 --> 00:18:05,452
Big brother?

367
00:18:05,519 --> 00:18:07,454
Killua: Yeah. It’s your big--

368
00:18:07,521 --> 00:18:09,056
( gasps )

369
00:18:09,122 --> 00:18:11,558
Alluka: Did you make nanika cry?

370
00:18:11,625 --> 00:18:13,160
Did you?

371
00:18:13,227 --> 00:18:16,764
Killua: Uh, oh, well, I mean...

372
00:18:16,830 --> 00:18:20,367
Alluka: She’s all curled up now
and crying her eyes out!

373
00:18:20,434 --> 00:18:22,403
Apologize to nanika!

374
00:18:22,469 --> 00:18:24,371
( Killua stammers ) But then--

375
00:18:24,438 --> 00:18:25,673
alluka: Go say you’re sorry!

376
00:18:25,739 --> 00:18:27,574
If you’re nice to me,

377
00:18:27,641 --> 00:18:31,545
that means you have to be nice
to nanika, too! Okay?

378
00:18:33,247 --> 00:18:36,150
( Killua gasps )

379
00:18:40,254 --> 00:18:42,790
Alluka: If you wanna protect me
like you say you do,

380
00:18:42,856 --> 00:18:45,559
you have to protect nanika, too!

381
00:18:46,827 --> 00:18:48,395
( Killua gasps )

382
00:18:48,462 --> 00:18:51,198
Alluka: But if you’re
going to be mean to nanika,

383
00:18:51,265 --> 00:18:53,100
I hate you!

384
00:18:54,168 --> 00:18:55,202
( Hands slap )

385
00:18:55,269 --> 00:18:57,471
( Alluka crying )

386
00:19:01,475 --> 00:19:05,245
killua: Alluka,
thank you for saying that.

387
00:19:05,312 --> 00:19:09,650
i guess big brother ill
was still in my head somewhere.

388
00:19:09,716 --> 00:19:14,221
But everything is okay now.

389
00:19:15,789 --> 00:19:18,425
can you please
bring nanika back out?

390
00:19:20,494 --> 00:19:21,729
Alluka: Mm-hmm.

391
00:19:28,435 --> 00:19:30,103
( Exhales )

392
00:19:34,308 --> 00:19:36,577
Killua: Nanika, I apologize.

393
00:19:36,643 --> 00:19:39,146
What I did was wrong.

394
00:19:39,213 --> 00:19:40,581
I’m sorry!

395
00:19:40,647 --> 00:19:45,318
I’ve just been afraid
of brother ill for so long.

396
00:19:45,385 --> 00:19:49,189
Doing what he said,
I hated every second.

397
00:19:49,256 --> 00:19:51,525
And now it’s not just me.

398
00:19:51,592 --> 00:19:55,496
He wants to force you to do
things against your will, too,

399
00:19:55,562 --> 00:19:57,364
and I got scared.

400
00:19:58,799 --> 00:20:02,202
I convinced myself
it was for alluka,

401
00:20:02,269 --> 00:20:04,404
and I was so mean to you.

402
00:20:04,471 --> 00:20:07,607
Forgive me, please!

403
00:20:10,177 --> 00:20:11,211
Nanika...

404
00:20:11,278 --> 00:20:14,148
I promise that i’ll protect you.

405
00:20:14,214 --> 00:20:15,615
I won’t leave you!

406
00:20:15,682 --> 00:20:18,318
But don’t Grant
other people’s wishes.

407
00:20:18,385 --> 00:20:21,622
i’ll always be there
to praise you whenever you want.

408
00:20:21,688 --> 00:20:24,858
So please come out,

409
00:20:24,925 --> 00:20:27,795
for me, just one more time?

410
00:20:40,274 --> 00:20:41,208
Nanika: ’kay.

411
00:20:48,482 --> 00:20:51,719
Killua: Nanika, will you...

412
00:20:51,785 --> 00:20:54,221
Please forgive me for being...

413
00:20:55,722 --> 00:20:57,624
Such a bad big brother?

414
00:20:58,692 --> 00:21:00,194
Nanika: Okay.

415
00:21:04,231 --> 00:21:05,165
( Sighs )

416
00:21:07,201 --> 00:21:09,136
I...

417
00:21:09,203 --> 00:21:11,472
Love you, killua.

418
00:21:14,641 --> 00:21:16,209
Mrs. Zoldyck: Tsubone,

419
00:21:16,276 --> 00:21:18,812
killua’s been released
from his precaution level.

420
00:21:18,879 --> 00:21:21,582
Please let them know, will you?

421
00:21:22,716 --> 00:21:23,750
Tsubone: Yes.

422
00:21:23,817 --> 00:21:26,820
I would be happy
to oblige, madam.

423
00:21:28,622 --> 00:21:29,823
♪

